---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Japanese Mythology — Ancient Terms That Score Big"
  description="Japanese mythology words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. SHOGUN (10pts), SAMURAI (9pts), HAIKU (12pts). Eastern vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble japanese words, shogun scrabble points, samurai scrabble, haiku scrabble, japanese mythology scrabble, eastern terms scrabble, zen scrabble words"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Japanese Mythology — Ancient Terms That Score Big","description":"Japanese mythology words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. SHOGUN (10pts), SAMURAI (9pts), HAIKU (12pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-mythology-japanese"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is SHOGUN a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! SHOGUN scores 10 points (S=1, H=4, O=1, G=2, U=1, N=1) in Scrabble. It means a military commander in feudal Japan. Valid in both TWL and SOWPODS dictionaries."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you play SAMURAI in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. SAMURAI scores 9 points (S=1, A=1, M=3, U=1, R=1, A=1, I=1) as a 7-letter bingo candidate. It refers to warriors of feudal Japan's military class."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is HAIKU valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! HAIKU scores 12 points (H=4, A=1, I=1, K=5, U=1). It's a 5-letter word referring to the traditional Japanese poetry form of 17 syllables. The K=5 and H=4 give it punch."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Japanese Mythology — Ancient Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Japanese mythology and culture have gifted the English language dozens of words now valid in Scrabble. From feudal warriors to poetic forms, these Eastern terms often contain K tiles and H tiles that deliver surprising point totals from familiar-sounding words.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">12 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">HAIKU</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">10 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">SHOGUN</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">9 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">SAMURAI</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">11 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">KIMONO</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring Japanese Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">HAIKU — 12 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">H=4, A=1, I=1, K=5, U=1 · 5 letters · High points per tile</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">A traditional Japanese poetic form of three lines with 5-7-5 syllables. HAIKU packs 12 points into just 5 tiles — an excellent 2.4 points per tile ratio. The K=5 and H=4 carry the weight.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⚔️ SHOGUN</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 pts · S=1, H=4, O=1, G=2, U=1, N=1 · Military lord</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🥋 SAMURAI</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts · S=1, A=1, M=3, U=1, R=1, A=1, I=1 · Bingo candidate</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">👘 KIMONO</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">11 pts · K=5, I=1, M=3, O=1, N=1, O=1 · Traditional robe</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🧘 ZEN</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 pts · Z=10, E=1, N=1 · Buddhist meditation</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Japanese Scrabble Words</h2>
      <p>Japanese loanwords offer excellent scoring from tiles that often sit unused on your rack:</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TOFU</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">KARATE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SAKE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SUMO</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">NINJA</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Japanese Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">SAMURAI is a natural bingo:</span> At exactly 7 letters, SAMURAI (9pts + 50 bonus = 59pts) uses very common tiles. Keep S, A, M, U, R on your rack and look for A, I to complete it.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">HAIKU maximises the K tile:</span> With K=5 and H=4, HAIKU scores 12 from just 5 tiles. Play it when you need to dump vowels while keeping your score respectable.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">ZEN is a Z-tile lifesaver:</span> At only 3 letters, ZEN (12pts) is one of the highest-scoring short words. Perfect for tight board positions where longer Z words won't fit.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Japanese loanwords are <span class="text-white font-medium">K-tile and vowel-heavy specialists</span>. HAIKU, KARATE, KIMONO, and SAKE all use K=5 with multiple vowels. When you're stuck with vowels plus K, think Japanese — these words turn a weak rack into solid scores.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-mythology/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Mythology</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-martial-arts/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Martial Arts</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-mythology-norse/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Norse Mythology</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid Japanese loanword instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
